9/9 Loving: We believe in our hearts that the message of Spesh “Ur Special” should be extended to all beings. We share that loving vibration in all our interactions.
8/9 Unique: We cherish each person’s idiosyncrasies that make them speshul. Our community is inclusive of all and we treasure each other’s weirdness.
7/9 Helpful: We are gracious hosts. When others are curious about our project or the brand, we welcome them in and enthusiastically share what lights us up about the project.
6/9 Soulful: Like a warm bowl of ramen soup, our community is a nourishing place to warm your soul. We leave interactions with our community with our cups full.
5/9 Entertaining: We cultivate an environment of fun. Where we can get together (on Discord or Twitter or IRL) and laugh and smile and enjoy our precious lives.

4/9 Proactive: We identify opportunities to grow or strengthen our community and we pursue those opportunities without waiting or asking for permission (hosting spaces, organizing IRL get-togethers, hosting community events, etc.)
3/9 Supportive: We seek to lift each other up. We want others to be well, to be happy, and to be successful. We offer our friendship and help wherever we can.
2/9 Respectful: We treat everyone like we would want to be treated. We create a safe environment where all (team, community, newcomers, etc.) can feel safe and free from judgment or attack.
1/9 Understanding: We value everyone’s perspective. When opinions differ, we seek to build bridges. We lead with inquiry and an aim to understand where others are coming from.

13/13 We hope that by providing this in depth explanation about the DDoS attack, we are able to alleviates concerns some of our holders had. We also hope this can help any other projects who may in the future experience DDoS attacks like this💕

12/13 To those impacted ➞ 

For anyone who was impacted by the metadata changes in a significant way, the team has been committed to doing what we can to make it right. If you have visual proof of being affected by this, please visit our Discord and open a support ticket.
11/13 3. We extensively tested to ensure that after we pushed the final update the database would be completely aligned & any error that occurred during the crash was automatically fixed.
10/13 2. During the second and third update we introduced a rate limit slowly to start to assigning metadata again. The server was then able to stay online & slowly recover from the misalignment.

9/13 Steps we took ➞ 

1. We immediately pushed the first update to the server which stopped assigning metadata to give us time to work on the alignment. No new metadata for marketplaces was available.
8/13 This resulted in multiple writes without removing the selected metadata from the pool (example: duplicate case), or no writing at all (example: 1/1 case).
7/13 During the crash the server was restarting & failing, causing the misalignment in the database. The server continued to get interrupted while writing.

6/13 However, due to the more complex nature of the Babies collection, w/ the ability to "save" the Babies being held by Spesh Holders, we need dynamic pools to assign the metadata since the claim is open ended.
5/13 In a standard drop where all the metadata is randomly assigned before reveal, an attack like this would cause downtime, but no misalignment as everything is already written in the DB.

4/13 Details on what occurred ➞ 

Our server experienced a DDoS attack shortly after reveal began, pinging the server with millions of requests. This caused the server to crash, leading to errors in the distribution & misalignment of the database.

3/13 To confirm your final metadata, please refresh your OS listing 3-4 times both on the metadata refresh button + your browser. There are no longer any duplicates (evil twins) in the collection, each piece is unique as anticipated!✨
2/13 The database was extensively tested and we can confirm that no future metadata changes have and will occur based on our testing, all NFTs are locked in to their random assignments.

1/13 As of Friday 7/22, we announced that all metadata is officially settled! It’s been amazing to see the reactions to the Babies collection💜 That said, we understand the frustration that some have experienced during the reveal. We truly apologize for the stress this caused.

Babies Reveal Recap Thread🧵

As many of you know, during our reveal we experienced a DDoS attack causing issues with our server leading to a temporary misalignment in the database. This has since been resolved, but for full disclosure on what occurred, read our thread below!
